cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.RO 

This paper focuses on video action recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed dynamic graph module is a novel approach to modeling object interactions in videos, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning and graph theory. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as well. Additionally, the paper uses the Something-Something dataset, which is a popular benchmark for video action recognition in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the proposed module has the ability to process streaming videos, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) applications.
